items.title: Can DRL’s new product launches offset the slowdown in Revlimid sales?
items.description: Dr Reddy's Laboratories saw a high single-digit revenue increase in Q3, driven by India, emerging, and European markets, despite a muted US business. The company launched 24 new products, with a pipeline of 100 products expected to offset slowing Revlimid sales. Analysts remain cautious, with valuations factoring in earnings upside.

items.title: Indian Oil Q2 Results: State-run refiner swings to Rs 7,818 crore profit, revenue up 4% YoY
items.description: State-run Indian Oil Corporation Ltd (IOC) on Monday reported its swing back to profit in the September quarter, posting a consolidated net profit attributable to shareholders at Rs 7,817.55 crore for second quarter of FY26, reversing from a loss of Rs 169.58 crore in the same quarter last year, as revenue rose and margins improved.

items.title: Adani Energy Q2 Results: Cons profit falls 21% YoY to Rs 534 crore, revenue rises 7%
items.description: Adani Energy Q2 Results: Adani Energy Solutions on Monday reported 21% decline in its consolidated net profit at Rs 534 crore for the quarter ended September 2025. The same stood at Rs 675 crore in the year-ago quarter. Revenue from operations in the same period increased 7% year-on-year (YoY) to Rs 6,596 crore.

items.title: Tata Investment Corp Q2 Results: Cons PAT rises 19% to Rs 148 crore, revenue up 8.5% YoY
items.description: In a remarkable showcase of resilience, Tata Investment Corporation has revealed impressive financial results. The net profit for Q2 of FY 2026 surged by 19.3%, complemented by a notable rise in operational revenue. This achievement coincides with heightened excitement from investors regarding the Tata Sons listing.

items.title: Tamilnad Mercantile Bank Q2 profit up 5% as lower provisions aid earnings
items.description: Tamilnad Mercantile Bank posted a 5% rise in Q2FY26 net profit to Rs 318 crore, aided by sharply lower provisions. Asset quality improved, with gross NPA falling to 1.01% and net NPA to 0.26%.

items.title: PNB Housing Finance Q2 Results: Profit rises 24% to Rs 582 crore
items.description: PNB Housing Finance on Monday reported a 24 per cent increase in its net profit to Rs 582 crore for the second quarter ended September 2025.

items.title: Bata India Q2 Results: Net profit down 73% to Rs 13.9 crore
items.description: Footwear maker Bata India Ltd on Monday reported a 73.26 per cent decline in consolidated net profit to Rs 13.9 crore in the second quarter ended September 30, 2025, impacted by lower revenue and higher expenses.

items.title: Canara HSBC Life Q2 Results: Net profit rises 11% to Rs 41 crore
items.description: Canara HSBC Life Insurance Company on Monday reported an 11 per cent rise in net profit to Rs 41 crore in the September quarter of the current fiscal.
